<title>USA: Crown Crafts Inc Q3 Dec 29 net falls.</title>
<headline>Crown Crafts Inc Q3 Dec 29 net falls.</headline>
<dateline>ATLANTA 1997-01-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Crown Crafts Inc.</p>
<p>					   For The Three Months Ended</p>
<p>				     Dec 29, 1996	  Dec 31, 1995</p>
<p> Net Sales			  $72,887,000	   $62,209,000</p>
<p> Net Earnings			 1,425,000	     2,095,000</p>
<p> Earnings Per Share			0.18		    0.26</p>
<p> Average Shares Outstanding     7,944,201	     7,944,094</p>
<p>					     For The Nine Months Ended</p>
<p>				     Dec 29, 1996	  Dec 31, 1995</p>
<p> Net Sales			  192,135,000	   158,746,000</p>
<p> Net Earnings			 2,003,000	     4,669,000</p>
<p> Earnings Per Share			0.25		    0.57</p>
<p> Average Shares Outstanding     7,944,201	     8,185,330</p>
<p>-- New York Newsdesk 212 859-1610  </p>
<p>NOTE: 1996 Q3 earnings are after a $1.9 million pretax, or $0.19 per share, charge due to a product recall and the closing of two small subsidiaries.</p>
<p>The charge is due to a reserve established for losses reltaed to the product recall of products made by Crown Craft's 51-percent owned Hans Benjamin Furniture Inc subsidiary and the company's planned exit from certain product categories.</p>
